**82. Remove Duplicates from Sorted List II**

#### **APPROACH -**
*Create a **dummyHead** with `dummyHead->next = head`
Traverse through the linked list with intially `isDuplicate = false`
Move through the nodes till same valued nodes present and update **isDuplicate**
Set the new links based on whether the current node is a duplicate
Return **dummyHead->next***
</br>
#### **COMPLEXITY -**
* Time Complexity : O(N)
* Space Complexity : O(1)
</br>
#### **CODE -**
```
class Solution {
public:
    ListNode* deleteDuplicates(ListNode* head) {
        ListNode *dummyHead = new ListNode(0, head);
        ListNode *prev = dummyHead, *curr = head;

        while(curr) {
            bool isDuplicate = false;
            while(curr->next && curr->val == curr->next->val) {
                isDuplicate = true;
                curr = curr->next;
            }
            if(isDuplicate)
                prev->next = curr->next;
            else
                prev = curr;
            curr = curr->next;
        }

        return dummyHead->next;
    }
};
```

