ok lets do this!!
i see a lot of people unabe to explain the question and the solution!
let me first explain the question!!
question says to remove the duplicates from an sorted linked list!
(piece of advice-whenever you are given a sorted ds ,this is a hint that the question is easy....so dont think too much)
anyways lets see some ex:
1->2->2->3->3->4;
we are required to remove ALL THE DUPLICATES ;
thus final list would be
1->4
and not
1->2->3->4;

so lets go into the solution!
like any other linked list problem lets take two pointer,
one fast and one slow!
the fast and slow both move one step at a time but fast is always ahead of slow as fast starts one node further than slow in the beginning!
LOGIC AND INTUITION:
"thus the function of our fast node is to search for duplicates and wait for slow to catch up before moving any further!
in other words whenever fast detects a duplicate it would keep traversing till the last duplicate and then wait..
the slow pointer will remove(delete) all the duplicate in the way and finally come to  fast node!
this process continues till the fast encounters a null value indicating end of linkedl list"

INITIALLY WE ALSO NEED A DUMMY NODE SO THAT FAST IS ONE STEP AHEAD OF SLOW!

```
public class Solution {
public ListNode deleteDuplicates(ListNode head) {
    ListNode dummy = new ListNode(0), fast = head, slow = dummy;
    slow.next = fast;
    while(fast != null) {
    	while (fast.next != null && fast.val == fast.next.val) { // this loop basically takes fast to end of the current duplicates that we are tracking
     		fast = fast.next;   
    	}
    	if (slow.next != fast) { 
    		slow.next = fast.next; //remove the duplicates.
    		fast = slow.next;     //fast moves to next unique value .
    	} else { //no duplicates...lets move towards right!!.
    		slow = slow.next;
    		fast = fast.next;
    	}

    }
    return dummy.next;
} }


