# Approach 1 - Using HashMap
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We can use a hashmap and store the frequency of elements and recreate the linked list by taking the elements occurring once.

But for that we have to traverse the linked list twice and we will not use the fact that the given linked list is sorted.

# Approach 2 - Two pointer
$$ Optimized \hspace{0.2cm} solution $$
<!-- This is the actual solution in the code. -->
We can use the given condition that the linked list is sorted and use two pointers to keep track of repeated nodes.

Keep a `count` variable and keep track of number of occurances of nodes.

Traverse through the linked list and add the elements which occur only once to the new linked list.
> **Optimization:** Can modify the given linked list without using extra space.

Note: Don't forget to check for the last element of the linked list.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```C++ []
class Solution {

public:
    ListNode* deleteDuplicates(ListNode* head) {
        if (head == NULL || head->next == NULL) return head;

        ListNode *curr = head, *prev = NULL;
        ListNode *r_head = NULL, *r_tail = NULL;

        int cnt = 0;
        while (curr != NULL) {
            if (prev == NULL || prev->val == curr->val) {
                ++cnt;
            } else {
                if (cnt < 2) {
                    if (r_head == NULL) {
                        r_head = new ListNode(prev->val);
                        r_tail = r_head;
                    } else {
                        r_tail->next = new ListNode(prev->val);
                        r_tail = r_tail->next;
                    }
                }
                cnt = 1;
            }
            prev = curr;
            curr = curr->next;
        }
        // To check for the last element of linked list
        if (cnt < 2 && prev != NULL) {
            if (r_head == NULL) {
                r_head = new ListNode(prev->val);
            } else {
                r_tail->next = new ListNode(prev->val);
            }
        }
        return r_head;
    }
};
```
